 <div class="on-this-page">
<div class="pullquote right">
                        <p>
                            The 24-hour service on route 365 will provide valuable night time links for residents of Havering
                            
                        </p>
                    </div>
                
            
            
            <p>The route, which runs between the Mardyke Estate and Havering Park, will run every half hour between 00.30 and 05.00 every night of the week.</p>
<p>The changes will bring night time bus services to South Hornchurch for the first time and provide links to Romford and Collier Row.</p>
<p>John Barry, Head of Network Development, London Buses, said: 'The 24-hour service on route 365 will provide valuable night time links for residents of Havering and is an important addition to London's expanding night bus network.'</p>
<p>The number of night bus services in London has increased significantly in recent years with passenger numbers more than doubling since 2000.</p>
<p>Almost half the users are people travelling to or from work.</p>
            <p><strong>Notes to editors:</strong></p>
<ul type="circle">
<li>Route 365 currently runs about every 12 minutes during the day, Monday to Saturday, and about every 20 minutes during the evenings and on Sundays </li>
<li>All London buses have in-vehicle CCTV and all except the Heritage Routemasters are accessible to wheelchair users </li>
<li>With over 8000 buses on approximately 700 routes the London bus network has seen usage increase by 52 per cent since 1999/2000</li></ul>
<p><br></p>

     

        
        
        
